import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    for entity in data['Entity'].unique():
        entity_data = data[data['Entity'] == entity]
        plt.plot(entity_data['Year'], entity_data['Deaths'], label=entity)

    plt.title('What is the trend of deaths caused by disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].sum().reset_index()
    ax = data_grouped.plot.bar(x='Entity', y='Deaths', legend=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of deaths caused by different types of disasters?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Disaster Type')
    plt.ylabel('Total Deaths')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    mean_deaths = data.groupby('Entity')['Deaths'].mean().reset_index()
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(mean_deaths['Entity'], mean_deaths['Deaths'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Entity')
    ax.set_ylabel('Mean Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the average number of deaths caused by each type of disaster?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Mean Deaths'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['Year'], data['Deaths'], c=data['Entity'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Deaths')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between the number of deaths and the year?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Entities")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year

    yearly_disasters = data.groupby(['Year', 'Entity']).size().reset_index(name='Count')
    pivot_data = yearly_disasters.pivot_table(index='Year', columns='Entity', values='Count', fill_value=0)

    ax = pivot_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(15, 7))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of disasters over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Disasters')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Disaster Types', loc='upper left')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
